We came for dinner - at the all you can eat shabu shabu. This was absolutely delicious, cleanly, and great variety. We chose to sit at a table to share a large hot pot with 2 broths - original and spicy. We loved the balance of the two broths. It includes a drink for each person. You can have pork belly, ribeye or chicken included - other meats are extra. On the conveyer you could get your choice of vegetables, fish balls, shrimp, bamboo shoots, quail eggs, dumplings, etc. The waitstaff is attentive and courteous. The price was reasonable for all you get!

My family and friends love this place. Sanitary in picking the items off the conveyor belt. So much variety in soup boths, fresh vegetables, noodles and different kinds of meats and seafood.. If you love to eat you will get $$$ worth!! Plus you can earn points and redeem it.

The service I got here was great! I came in a little after 4, just when their lunch buffet ends, but I explained to the waitress that I'm a vegetarian and that it's only a little after the meal time and if she would give me the lunch-time price it would be really great and she happily offered :-). A good restaurant is when they try to accommodate as much as they can, and they really did that for me here, the food was good quality, now granted, I only ate the vegetables, but they were totally fine for me. Also, their sauce bar contains a nice variety of flavors.

Location is ideal being across from Walmart so free parking. Had several different broth base to start out with and you can adjust it to your taste by adding items from the sauce station. Sauce station had impressive number of items to mix and match with helpful sauce recipes on the wall. If you need more broth, they will bring it out to you and even willing to help you with the hot pot. There's a conveyor with all the non meat items constantly rotating and items being added that you can add to your hot pot including shrimp, fish cakes, dumplings, mushrooms and numerous other items. It is pricey (about $30 for adult) for all you can eat but if you eat a lot, the price is worth it.

Pretty pricey. $18 for lunch all-you-can-eat for adults, $16 or so for kids. However, the kids meal comes with a drink and a little dessert, so super cute. And if your little one likes veggies, then this is the joint for sure! Corn on the cob, little Japanese sausages, or arabiki, fish cake or kamaboko, and a variety of fun vegetables like snow peas and zucchini, make this a favorite for the little kids we know. the Miso soup option is mild and comes with tofu. A nice option for little kids, if they don't like a strong Seafood flavor or if they don't like anything hot or super salty. Seafood broth comes with clams, which are in your soup. Love that!  We went on a weekday for lunch, and the servers there were super helpful and kind. Little difficult to understand the accent, but that's okay.  Uses the five-star app. Check there for a discount. Make sure that the points are rewarded though-- sometimes the very nice cashier does forget. Try to pay with cash and maybe you'll get an extra discount.  Recommend for families and groups. Ask about MSG sensitivity though. Love the fresh food and the little clear plastic cloches on the dishes.  Park on-street for the best deal. There is a validated parking lot, but it's pricey.

Really a nice place to go when you are hungry with an awesome all you can eat deal.  The place is set up very nice with a conveyor system that has a constant supply of fresh veggies, fish balls and dumplings.  Fresh meats including rib eye, lamb and pork can be requested from your server.  The kitchen is very clean and clearly visible through the large window on the back wall.  Lots of patio seating on the front of the store.  This place is located in the new 808 building across from the Wal-Mart garage on the bottom floor.  They offer free valet parking in a unique elevator parking system.  Very reasonable food and beverage pricing.  We had all you can eat for two was under 60 bucks and we stayed about 2 hours.  We loved this place and recommend it to others.

Overall liked this place but it's usually crowded and understaffed with only 2 servers. Can be hard to get their attention at times since they're running around trying to do everything by themselves. Definitely feel for the employees. Recommendations would be to avoid the spicy "mild" soup if you're not a fan super spicy things. As a jalapeno enthusiast it was too much for even myself. Highly recommend getting a reservation beforehand. And lastly, don't be afraid to wave down the servers to get their attention, just be nice about it. Otherwise, this place is great for tourists and locals.

I didn't really know what to expect when I came here besides knowing that it was a hot pot place with personal hot pots.  Despite the shabu shabu in its name, this place definitely had a Chinese style hot pot experience.  The tables doubled as the heating elements and you could choose to either have individual pots or share a big pot with everyone in your party.  The all you can eat price includes meat and all your typical hot pot fare which came to you on a conveyor belt (not unlike some sushi restaurants).  The selection of broth wasn't very extensive, but they did have plenty of ingredients for you to concoct a dipping sauce to your liking as well as a good selection of meats (though some incurred additional costs).  I also very much enjoyed my miso soup base and unlimited sweet green tea.  Honestly, pretty good hot pot experience, but the service was a bit spotty despite it being a fairly small venue.  At least on our visit, it took a few tries to flag the wait staff down for soup refills and check.
